{
  "metadata": {
    "type": "targeted_grid",
    "name": "cost_floor_asymmetric_test",
    "description": "Tests Proposal 3 (Hayes 2019 cost floor) in the regime where it has maximum impact: asymmetric hashrate split (v27=25%, v26=75%).\nAt hashrate_split=0.25, v27 starts at a 3:1 hashrate disadvantage. As pools cascade toward the winning fork, the losing fork sheds hashrate rapidly. The cost floor scales with hashrate_weight \u2014 so as a fork loses hashrate its price floor drops proportionally, making the cascade faster and more decisive.\nCost floor comparison at key hashrate levels:\n  hashrate=0.75 \u2192 floor = $42,750  (vs baseline $48,000 \u2014 small difference)\n  hashrate=0.50 \u2192 floor = $28,500  (vs baseline $48,000 \u2014 $19,500 gap)\n  hashrate=0.25 \u2192 floor = $14,250  (vs baseline $48,000 \u2014 $33,750 gap)\n  hashrate=0.00 \u2192 floor = $0       (vs baseline $48,000 \u2014 total collapse)\n\nRun BOTH in parallel \u2014 two namespaces, same scenarios:\n\n  Sweep A \u2014 baseline oracle:\n    python 3_run_sweep.py \\\n      --input cost_floor_asymmetric_test/build_manifest.json \\\n      --namespace sweep-floor-base \\\n      --results-dir cost_floor_asymmetric_test/results_baseline \\\n      --duration 2500 --retarget-interval 144 --interval 2\n\n  Sweep B \u2014 cost floor active:\n    python 3_run_sweep.py \\\n      --input cost_floor_asymmetric_test/build_manifest.json \\\n      --namespace sweep-floor-active \\\n      --results-dir cost_floor_asymmetric_test/results_floor \\\n      --duration 2500 --retarget-interval 144 --interval 2 \\\n      --use-cost-floor\n\nNamespaces to create first:\n  kubectl create namespace sweep-floor-base\n  kubectl create namespace sweep-floor-active\n\nKey questions:\n  - Does the cost floor accelerate cascade timing (faster v27_block_share growth)?\n  - Does it change the winning fork at econ=0.60 where v27 starts hashrate-disadvantaged?\n  - Does reorg_mass change? Larger price gaps \u2192 stronger incentive to switch \u2192 fewer reorgs?\n",
    "spec_file": "specs/cost_floor_asymmetric_test.yaml",
